<div>
THE people of <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow" target="_blank">Glasgow</a> tonight paid a poignant tribute to Karen BuckleyHundreds gathered in George Square to pay their respects to the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people" target="_blank">Irish</a> student just two hours after a man appeared in court charged with her murderLess than a mile away from the court a large crowd assembled in the heart of the city to remember Karen 24 from Mallow County CorkA lone piper played Amazing Grace during the event as dozens of floral tributes and lit <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Candle" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Candle" target="_blank">candles</a> were left at the foot of the Scott MonumentA <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cork_%28city%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cork_%28city%29" target="_blank">Cork</a> man also sang a moving rendition of the county anthem Banks of My Own Lovely LeeKaren's mum Marian dad John and brothers all arrived after the vigil There were emotional scenes as Marian was comforted by her family and localsGlasgow Caledonian University GCU  where Miss Buckley was studying occupational health  was well represented with many young people in attendance wearing GCU tracksuits and jumpersThe vigil was organised by former <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_people" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_people" target="_blank">Scottish</a> Socialist politician Rosie KaneShe said &quotI don't want to be here that's the first thing I need to say&quotIt seems that everyone has been devastated but we want to support Karen's family and show them the best side of the city We're trying to make something beautiful from that horrible horrible grief&quotThere have been some songs from <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland" target="_blank">Scotland</a> and <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland" target="_blank">Ireland</a> and people have brought flowers and <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Candle" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Candle" target="_blank">candles</a>&quotWe also had a moment's silence to think about Karen's life what we knew of her about her family and to wish them the best&quotThe case has touched many people in <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland" target="_blank">Scotland</a> and <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland" target="_blank">Ireland</a> with services held in Miss Buckley's home town of <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cork_%28city%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cork_%28city%29" target="_blank">Cork</a> earlier this weekBarry Ahearn who is originally from <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cork_%28city%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cork_%28city%29" target="_blank">Cork</a> but now lives in <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland" target="_blank">Scotland</a> travelled from his home in Ayr to pay his respects to Miss Buckley in George SquareAs organisers appealed for anyone who wanted to address the large crowd Mr Ahearn sang a local <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cork_%28city%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cork_%28city%29" target="_blank">Cork</a> songHe said &quotI've been living in <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland" target="_blank">Scotland</a> for the last four years and wanted to come today to show solidarity and support for Karen's family&quotI sang On The Banks On My Own Lovely Lee  it's the river that runs through <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cork_%28city%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cork_%28city%29" target="_blank">Cork</a> and is the local anthem&quotThe whole situation is so sad particularly when you're living in <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland" target="_blank">Scotland</a> and something like this happens to someone from your own country It just doesn't fit it's so sad&quotHis wife Maura said &quotIt has really touched us this week it's so sad and we all feel it very much&quotThere's a great number of people here tonight who I'm sure feel the same and we just want to rally round the Buckley family&quotFlowers and messages have also been left at the GCU campus and at the entrance to High Craigton Farm to the north of <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow" target="_blank">Glasgow</a> where the student's body was foundPoliticians took time out of campaigning earlier today to offer their condolences to the Buckley familyScotland's First Minister Nicola Sturgeon said &quotMy thoughts are very much with the family and friends of Karen Buckley&quotJim Murphy began Labour's <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_people" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_people" target="_blank">Scottish</a> manifesto launch in <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow" target="_blank">Glasgow</a> by saying &quotMy thoughts and the thoughts of everyone in the room go out to Karen's family None of us can in anyway imagine the pain and horror that they are going through&quotGlasgow and <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland" target="_blank">Scotland</a> stands with you&quot 
</div>
